description.narrative: Throughout 2019, 490,142 vulnerable children (234,599 girls; 255,543 boys) were identified and referred to basic protection services, notably thanks to improved collaboration and cooperation between social service providers and community-based actors. This brings the total number of vulnerable children referred to basic protection services to 3,726,147, during the country programme cycle. To capitalize on existing community-based child protection practices, UNICEF commissioned, an in-depth study on the ‘protective community' approach. These results, together with UNICEF's experience with the Psychosocial Assistants (APS) in the Ebola response, has shaped the development of a practical implementation guide and a training module for social para-workers. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
